  <BadgeInSentenceDemo />
</Example>

## API Reference

### Badge

Displays a small label for status, categorization, or metadata.

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `variant` | `"primary" \| "secondary" \| "error" \| "warning" \| "success" \| "info" \| "beta" \| "outline" \| "neutral" \| "red" \| "orange" \| "green" \| "teal" \| "teal-subtle" \| "blue" \| "purple" \| "destructive"` | No | Color variant. Defaults to `"primary"`. |
| `appearance` | `"filled" \| "dot"` | No | Visual appearance. Defaults to `"filled"`. |
| `children` | `Snippet` | Yes | Badge label content. |
| `class` | `string` | No | Additional classes merged with the badge styles. |

All other props are passed to the underlying `<span>` element.
